# Deepsuck Harness — Data Model

> The harness is the runtime container that enforces DAG-first behavior. SOUL.md is the constitution. These entities define what the harness tracks and enforces.

---

## Core Entities

### Entity: SOUL

The constitution file loaded at agent startup as system prompt prefix.

```yaml
entity: SOUL
type: entity
properties:
  path:
    type: string
    required: true
  lines:
    type: number
    required: true
  chars:
    type: number
    required: true
  tokens_est:
    type: number
    required: true
  dynamic:
    type: boolean
    required: true
  position:
    type: enum
    values: [system_prompt_prefix]
    required: true
states: [loaded, enforced]
lifecycle: loaded → enforced
```

### Entity: AuditTrapdoor

Self-audit that fires every 5 tool calls. Four diagnostic questions. Failure forces DAG reload.

```yaml
entity: AuditTrapdoor
type: entity
properties:
  trigger:
    type: enum
    values: [every_5_tool_calls]
    required: true
  question_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  fail_action:
    type: enum
    values: [reload_dag, block_response]
    required: true
states: [idle, triggered, passed, failed]
lifecycle: idle → triggered → passed → idle
```

### Entity: ConfidenceMarker

Appended to every code answer. Measures grounding against DAG entities.

```yaml
entity: ConfidenceMarker
type: entity
properties:
  format:
    type: string
    required: true
  threshold_grounded:
    type: number
    required: true
  threshold_partial:
    type: number
    required: true
states: [appended, verified]
lifecycle: appended → verified
```

### Entity: HardBlock

Immutable guardrail. Five walls. No exceptions. No workarounds.

```yaml
entity: HardBlock
type: entity
properties:
  count:
    type: number
    required: true
  enforcement:
    type: enum
    values: [absolute]
    required: true
  walls:
    type: string[]
    required: true
states: [active, violated]
lifecycle: active
```

### Entity: CompoundingLoop

Feedback loop: compile → validate → score report. Regression = block.

```yaml
entity: CompoundingLoop
type: entity
properties:
  trigger:
    type: enum
    values: [spec_file_edited]
    required: true
  commands:
    type: string[]
    required: true
  block_on_regression:
    type: boolean
    required: true
states: [idle, running, blocked]
lifecycle: idle → running → idle
```

### Entity: ToolRouter

Routing table for tool selection. Never grep for structure.

```yaml
entity: ToolRouter
type: entity
properties:
  rule_count:
    type: number
    required: true
  anti_pattern:
    type: string
    required: true
states: [enforcing]
lifecycle: enforcing
```

### Entity: Compile

The compilation process. Reads .dog files, produces .dag.

```yaml
entity: Compile
type: event
properties:
  source_files:
    type: number
    required: true
  output_hash:
    type: string
    required: true
  token_savings_pct:
    type: number
    required: false
states: [running, completed, failed]
lifecycle: running → completed
```

### Entity: DAG

Compiled spec graph. Deterministic JSON. Queryable by AI agents.

```yaml
entity: DAG
type: entity
properties:
  version:
    type: string
    required: true
  sha256:
    type: string
    required: true
  source_files:
    type: number
    required: true
  token_savings_pct:
    type: number
    required: false
states: [current, stale]
lifecycle: current → stale
```

---

## Relationships

### Relationship: Compile → DAG

```yaml
relationship: Compile → DAG
verb: produces
cardinality: 1:1
required: false
cascade: nullify
invariants: DAG is compiled output of all .dog files
```

### Relationship: SOUL → DAG

```yaml
relationship: SOUL → DAG
verb: references
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: SOUL.md truth hierarchy starts with DAG. No code read before DAG load
```

### Relationship: AuditTrapdoor → DAG

```yaml
relationship: AuditTrapdoor → DAG
verb: queries
cardinality: 1:1
required: true
cascade: restrict
invariants: Trapdoor must re-read .dag on failure. No proceeding without DAG verification
```
